DataElement.preferredName: Self-Organizing Map Type Y-Coordinate integer One Dimensional Array
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A data visualization technique which reduces the dimensions of data through the use of self-organizing neural networks. SOMs scale well to large data sets, can identify local clusters in the data and organize them globally, and proceed in an unsupervised fashion.:Something distinguishable as an identifiable class based on common qualities._A vertical coordinate that is used together with a horizontal coordinate to specify an exact point in space._Generic value domain for a single dimensional array with integers as elements.
